. Also If I right click on him he says he doesn't like my little gang... i'm a dwarf by the way. When I speak to him to trigger the quest he says the temple of life does not like me.<br>
<br>
1. How long can it take to earn faction?<br>
2. Is faction affected by race?<br>
3. Is faction affected by deity?<br>
3. Does race or deity prevent the performance of a quest?<br>
<br>
Oh and by the way I am after bone chips or bandit bands LOL<br>
<br>
Thanks, <p>Boradur <BR> 
Paladin and Knight of Truth</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fbe5b4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub44.ezboard.com/ulunitune.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Lunitune</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.fbe.unsw.edu.au/staff/graham.hannah/eq/resources/lunitune60x60.jpg BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 45<br> <font color=#8B4513>(4/3/01 11:09:00 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.fbe.unsw.edu.au/staff/graham.hannah/eq/resources/lunitune60x60.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Shining Star of Light Quest</span><hr size=1> Faction can take a looooooong time.  Ask Grogguk.  Can take thousands of mobs just to go from ready attack to dubious.<br>
<br>
Facting is indeed affected by race, that is the first and primary part of faction.  Eg DE cleric in cleric guild in RIvervale.<br>
<br>
Deity is the other primary faction determinant at the beginning.  Innoruk supporter is just not welcome in Faydwer.<br>
<br>
Race and deity don't themselves preclude the performance of quests, it is faction.  So, you can end up doing all sorts of quests in the bad areas if you kill enough good NPC's etc, or raise your faction enough giving away muffins and stuff.  The lady who kindly bound us adventures on Goladar the Brave's adventure into OOT was a lev 52 DE caster.  She was just glad to bind us for a bit of a change because she was running back and forth for I don't know how long delivering (muffins I think it was) stuff to get her faction up for a quest.<br>
<br>
I have heard and believe that anyone can do any quest, as long as they can get their faction up.<br>
<br>
However, because you are a nice dorf, you should not have too many issues with faction.  I imagine you have not killed any good guys.<br>
<br>
I have not come across particularly satisfactory faction information for what i want, however check out these addresses.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://everquest.allakhazam.com/">everquest.allakhazam.com/</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--><br>
And look for faction down the side.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://eq.castersrealm.com/data/factions.asp">eq.castersrealm.com/data/factions.asp</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--><br>
<br>
There is another website with a good faction database too, which I can't find for some reason.  Will post it when I find it.<br>
<br>
Also, Everlore has player comments by the quests which often give good advice on such things.<br>
<br>
Luni Luni <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fed995><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub44.ezboard.com/uboradur.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Boradur</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 28<br> <font color=#8B4513>(4/4/01 2:04:26 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.fbe.unsw.edu.au/staff/graham.hannah/eq/resources/boradur60x60.jpg  WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Shining Star of Light Quest</span><hr size=1> Wow thanks Luni!<br>
