Paladin and Knight of Truth</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fed995><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub44.ezboard.com/uwarninwraithlore.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Warnin Wraithlore</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.telusplanet.net/public/canadak/sig.JPG BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Administrator</span><br>  Posts: 320<br> <font color=#8B4513>(4/12/01 3:52:15 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.telusplanet.net/public/canadak/warnin1.JPG WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Shining Star of Light Quest</span><hr size=1> There is a great shield drop in Highpass hold on one of the Mucktails at the gnoll spawn.  Cracked Darkwood Shield, 13AC +9 strength!  May take several hours and a good group though, the item is farmed so most groups there don't have an NBG policy on looting, it is a roll.  I saw wizards roll on it, twinked wizards, while some poor fighter who had only fine steel weapons and ratty banded armour lost out on it after 5 1/2 hours of camping... oh wait that warrior was me (Grogguk).  Grrrrrrrr...<br>
<br>
But it is a good way to gain levels too.<br>
<br>
Congrats on the mace.  I may have to go after one of those.  I have bullsmasher (6/20) a wicked weapon for training 1hb.  I can solo some yellows with it too because of dam/delay ratio, but it is not magic.  I will need an upgrade to that soon.<br>
<br>
Also, for the future keep in mind you don't always have to talk to the people for the quest.  If you know what to do and what stuff to give who (I get info on <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://eq.stomped.com">eq.stomped.com</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> ) as long as you can walk up to them you can do it.  I know for bullsmasher the guy wouldn't talk to me but when I gave him the quest items he gave me the rewards.  Same with Grogguk and gnoll scalps in HH, All I needed to do was be able to walk up to the captain to give him the stuff, even though he wouldn't say a word to me he still let me do his little quest.  Great for faction.<br>
<br>
Anyway, again congrats on the marriage.  I hope you have a nice break and we await your return friend.<br>
<br>
